Available Tools: escalate_ticket | transfer_to_specialist | get_escalation_status | set_sla
Call Schema: { "func_call": "string", "ticket_id": "string", "reason": "string", "target_team": "string" }
Response Schema: { "ticket_id": "string", "escalated_to": "string", "reason": "string", "sla_hours": number, "status": "string" }
---
Question: Set a critical 2-hour SLA for ticket TKT-9921 regarding the payment gateway outage and assign it to the Level 3 Infrastructure team.
Call: { "func_call": "set_sla", "ticket_id": "TKT-9921", "reason": "Critical payment gateway outage affecting all transactions", "target_team": "Level 3 Infrastructure" }
Response: { "ticket_id": "TKT-9921", "escalated_to": "Level 3 Infrastructure", "reason": "Critical payment gateway outage affecting all transactions", "sla_hours": 2, "status": "SLA_ACTIVE_BREACH_WARNING" }

Question: Check the current escalation status for ticket TKT-8842 which was transferred to the Billing Disputes team yesterday.
Call: { "func_call": "get_escalation_status", "ticket_id": "TKT-8842", "reason": "Routine status check on billing dispute resolution", "target_team": "Billing Disputes" }
Response: { "ticket_id": "TKT-8842", "escalated_to": "Billing Disputes", "reason": "Routine status check on billing dispute resolution", "sla_hours": 24, "status": "RESOLVED_WITHIN_SLA" }

Question: Escalate ticket TKT-7733 immediately to the Security Ops team due to a suspected data breach and set a 1-hour response window.
Call: { "func_call": "escalate_ticket", "ticket_id": "TKT-7733", "reason": "Suspected data breach requiring immediate forensic analysis", "target_team": "Security Ops" }
Response: { "ticket_id": "TKT-7733", "escalated_to": "Security Ops", "reason": "Suspected data breach requiring immediate forensic analysis", "sla_hours": 1, "status": "CRITICAL_BREACH_IMMINENT" }

Question: Transfer ticket TKT-6654 to the Enterprise Account Specialists and apply a 4-hour SLA for the VIP client login failure.
